   "source": [
    "# Part 7: Conclusions and takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "In your own words describe the results of the notebook. Which model(s) performed the best on the dataset? Why do you think that is? Did anything surprise you about the exercise?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Answer:\n",
    "    \n",
    "The Neural Nerwork had the highest accuracy with this data set. this is because the other models had some downfalls with this data set and the fact that the data points couldn't be easily seperated. the two flowers virinica and versicolor had overlappinog data points which would make it more difficult to predict with the K-nearest neighbors and logistic regression models. this is because the k-nearest neighbors would incorrectly predict overlapping data points in the test set, and the SVM model tries to seperate the data which will also fail to predict overlapping data points. \n",
    "    \n",
    " What supprised me about this exercise was how simple the sklearn package makes developing AI models. In class we learn about the math behind how everything works and here all we need to do to implement them is a couple of simple functions."
   ]
